defs.docs: Zero-cost Futures in Rust

defs.name: Poll
defs.docs:
Return type of the `Future::poll` method, indicates whether a future's value
 is ready or not.

defs.name: Ready
defs.docs: Represents that a value is immediately ready.

defs.name: NotReady
defs.docs: Represents that a value is not ready yet, but may be so later.

defs.name: Async
defs.docs: Return type of future, indicating whether a value is ready or not.

defs.name: Ready
defs.docs:
The `start_send` attempt succeeded, so the sending process has
 *started*; you must use `Sink::poll_complete` to drive the send
 to completion.

defs.name: NotReady
defs.docs:
The `start_send` attempt failed due to the sink being full. The value
 being sent is returned, and the current `Task` will be automatically
 notified again once the sink has room.

defs.name: AsyncSink
defs.docs: The result of an asynchronous attempt to send a value to a sink.

defs.name: StartSend
defs.docs:
Return type of the `Sink::start_send` method, indicating the outcome of a
 send attempt. See `AsyncSink` for more details.

defs.name: future
defs.docs: Futures

defs.name: Empty
defs.docs: A future which is never resolved.

defs.name: empty
defs.docs:
Creates a future which never resolves, representing a computation that never
 finishes.

defs.name: Lazy
defs.docs:
A future which defers creation of the actual future until a callback is
 scheduled.

defs.name: lazy
defs.docs:
Creates a new future which will eventually be the same as the one created
 by the closure provided.

defs.name: PollFn
defs.docs: A future which adapts a function returning `Poll`.

defs.name: poll_fn
defs.docs: Creates a new future wrapping around a function returning `Poll`.

defs.name: FutureResult
defs.docs: A future representing a value that is immediately ready.

defs.name: result
defs.value: fn <T, E> (r: result::Result<T, E>) -> FutureResult<T, E>
defs.docs: Creates a new "leaf future" which will resolve with the given result.

defs.name: ok
defs.docs:
Creates a "leaf future" from an immediate value of a finished and
 successful computation.

defs.name: err
defs.docs: Creates a "leaf future" from an immediate value of a failed computation.

defs.name: Break
defs.docs: Indicates that the loop has completed with output `T`.

defs.name: Continue
defs.docs:
Indicates that the loop function should be called again with input
 state `S`.

defs.name: Loop
defs.docs: The status of a `loop_fn` loop.

defs.name: LoopFn
defs.docs: A future implementing a tail-recursive loop.

defs.name: loop_fn
defs.value: fn <S, T, A, F> (initial_state: S, mut func: F) -> LoopFn<A, F>
defs.docs: Creates a new future implementing a tail-recursive loop.

defs.name: AndThen
defs.docs:
Future for the `and_then` combinator, chaining a computation onto the end of
 another future which completes successfully.

defs.name: Flatten
defs.docs:
Future for the `flatten` combinator, flattening a future-of-a-future to get just
 the result of the final future.

defs.name: FlattenStream
defs.docs:
Future for the `flatten_stream` combinator, flattening a
 future-of-a-stream to get just the result of the final stream as a stream.

defs.name: Fuse
defs.docs: A future which "fuses" a future once it's been resolved.

defs.name: IntoStream
defs.docs:
Future that forwards one element from the underlying future
 (whether it is success of error) and emits EOF after that.

defs.name: Map
defs.docs: Future for the `map` combinator, changing the type of a future.

defs.name: MapErr
defs.docs: Future for the `map_err` combinator, changing the error type of a future.

defs.name: FromErr
defs.docs: Future for the `from_err` combinator, changing the error type of a future.

defs.name: OrElse
defs.docs:
Future for the `or_else` combinator, chaining a computation onto the end of
 a future which fails with an error.

defs.name: Select
defs.docs:
Future for the `select` combinator, waiting for one of two futures to
 complete.

defs.name: SelectNext
defs.docs: Future yielded as the second result in a `Select` future.

defs.name: Select2
defs.docs:
Future for the `select2` combinator, waiting for one of two differently-typed
 futures to complete.

defs.name: Then
defs.docs:
Future for the `then` combinator, chaining computations on the end of
 another future regardless of its outcome.

defs.name: A
defs.docs: First branch of the type

defs.name: B
defs.docs: Second branch of the type

defs.name: Either
defs.docs:
Combines two different futures yielding the same item and error
 types into a single type.

defs.name: Inspect
defs.docs: Do something with the item of a future, passing it on.

defs.name: CatchUnwind
defs.docs: Future for the `catch_unwind` combinator.

defs.name: JoinAll
defs.docs:
A future which takes a list of futures and resolves with a vector of the
 completed values.

defs.name: join_all
defs.docs:
Creates a future which represents a collection of the results of the futures
 given.

defs.name: SelectAll
defs.docs:
Future for the `select_all` combinator, waiting for one of any of a list of
 futures to complete.

defs.name: select_all
defs.docs: Creates a new future which will select over a list of futures.

defs.name: SelectOk
defs.docs:
Future for the `select_ok` combinator, waiting for one of any of a list of
 futures to successfully complete. Unlike `select_all`, this future ignores all
 but the last error, if there are any.

defs.name: select_ok
defs.docs: Creates a new future which will select the first successful future over a list of futures.

defs.name: Shared
defs.docs:
A future that is cloneable and can be polled in multiple threads.
 Use `Future::shared()` method to convert any future into a `Shared` future.

defs.name: SharedItem
defs.docs:
A wrapped item of the original future that is cloneable and implements Deref
 for ease of use.

defs.name: SharedError
defs.docs:
A wrapped error of the original future that is cloneable and implements Deref
 for ease of use.

defs.name: BoxFuture
defs.docs: A type alias for `Box<Future + Send>`
